constructor.details: This is a security measure for UUPS upgradeable contracts

createLendingPool((address,address,uint2.details: Deploys both a router and lending pool, configures interest rate model and liquidation parameters, and supplies initial liquidity. Requires caller to have approved sufficient borrow tokens.

params._lendingPoolParams: The parameters for the lending pool including tokens, rates, and thresholds

returns._0: The address of the newly created lending pool

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

initialize(address,address,address,addre.details: This function can only be called once due to the initializer modifier

params._isHealthy: The address of the IsHealthy contract
params._lendingPoolDeployer: The address of the lending pool deployer contract
params._lendingPoolRouterDeployer: The address of the router deployer contract
params._positionDeployer: The address of the position deployer contract
params._protocol: The address of the protocol contract

pause().details: Can only be called by addresses with PAUSER_ROLE

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

params._eid: The LayerZero endpoint ID corresponding to the chain

setDexRouter(address).details: Only callable by addresses with OWNER_ROLE

params._dexRouter: The address of the DEX router contract

setInterestRateModel(address).details: Only callable by addresses with OWNER_ROLE

params._interestRateModel: The address of the new interest rate model contract

setLendingPoolRouterDeployer(address).details: Only callable by addresses with OWNER_ROLE

params._lendingPoolRouterDeployer: The address of the new router deployer contract

setMinAmountSupplyLiquidity(address,uint.details: Only callable by addresses with OWNER_ROLE. This ensures pools have sufficient liquidity at creation.

params._minAmountSupplyLiquidity: The minimum amount of tokens required for initial liquidity

setOftAddress(address,address).details: Only callable by addresses with OWNER_ROLE. Used for cross-chain token transfers.

params._oftAddress: The address of the corresponding OFT wrapper

setOperator(address,bool).details: Only callable by addresses with OWNER_ROLE

params._operator: The address of the operator to update
params._status: The new status for the operator (true for active, false for inactive)

setPositionDeployer(address).details: Only callable by addresses with OWNER_ROLE

params._positionDeployer: The address of the new position deployer contract

setProtocol(address).details: Only callable by addresses with OWNER_ROLE

params._protocol: The address of the new protocol contract

setTokenDataStream(address).details: Only callable by addresses with OWNER_ROLE

params._tokenDataStream: The address of the data stream contract

setWrappedNative(address).details: Only callable by addresses with OWNER_ROLE. Examples: WETH, WMATIC, etc.

params._wrappedNative: The address of the wrapped native token

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See the corresponding https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165#how-interfaces-are-identified[ERC section] to learn more about how these ids are created. This function call must use less than 30 000 gas.

unpause().details: Can only be called by addresses with PAUSER_ROLE

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.
